Has to be at least one minor child in the home/or pregnant woman, and income at or below 200 percent of the federal poverty level.

They won‚Äôt have to provide verification of income they can self attest but it must be for an emergent need, example rent, utilities

They can apply at jfs.franklincountyohio.gov/covid19PRC

Academy for Urban Scholars has cancelled all classes beginning Monday, March 16th, through Friday, April 3, 2020 due to the executive Extended Three Week Spring Break order announced today by Governor Mike DeWine. The school will remain open on Friday, March 13, 2020. This will serve as our official spring break and will take the place of our regular Spring Break that was scheduled for April 10- April 17, 2020.

We will continue to monitor the development of COVID-19 and will plan accordingly, in partnership with local, state, and federal health and government officials. We will continue to communicate updates as we learn more. School will resume on Monday, April 6, 2020.

In an effort to ensure the safety of our staff all NCUS/AUS offices will be closed beginning Monday, March 16-Friday, March 20, 2020. Administration and NCUS staff will resume normal work hours on Monday, March 23, 2020.
--
Emmanuel D. Anthony M.Ed., MBA

Did you Know?!?
1983 Vanessa Williams became the first Black woman to be crowned Miss America. White supporters were not happy because she was Black and some Blacks didn‚Äôt believe the blue eyed beauty was ‚ÄúBlack enough‚Äù.

1984 Vanessa Williams became the first woman to give up the Miss America crown (at the request of the pageant organizers) after Penthouse magazine announced they would publish unauthorized photos of her.

2016 The CEO of the Miss America Pageant issued an apology to Vanessa Williams (32 years later üòí).

You are holding a cup of coffee when someone comes along and bumps into you ü§¶üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è or shakes your arm, making you spill your coffee everywhere.

Why did you spill the coffee? ü§î

"Well because someone bumped into me, of course!" ü§∑üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Wrong answer.

You spilled the coffee because there was coffee in your cup.

Had there been tea in the cup, you would have spilled tea.

*Whatever is inside the cup, is what will spill out.*

Therefore, when life comes along and shakes you (which WILL happen), whatever is inside you will come out. It's easy to fake it, until you get rattled.
*So we have to ask ourselves... ‚Äúwhat's in my cup?"

When life gets tough, what spills over?

Joy, gratefulness, peace and humility?üíì

Or anger, bitterness, harsh words and reactions? üí£

You choose! üíØ

Today let's work towards filling our cups with gratitude, forgiveness, joy, words of affirmation; and kindness, gentleness and love for others.üôåüèΩüôèüèΩ
